article.headline: Colgate 70, New Hampshire 66
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. (AP) -- Mark Linebaugh led four Raiders in double figures with 17 points to lead Colgate to a 70-66 win over New Hampshire on Friday. Colgate (3-2) jumped to a 38-26 lead in the first half paced by 6-10 shooting from behind the arc. The Raiders extended the lead to 18 at 55-37 five minutes into the second half. New Hampshire (2-3) cut the lead to seven on an 11-0 run with 10 minutes left. The Wildcats continued to climb back into the game, cutting the lead to one, 63-62, after a Craig Walls jumper with four minutes remaining. But Colgate regrouped on Jon Simon's five points in the final minutes. Walls scored 17 points and grabbed 14 rebounds in setting a career high for points and rebounds. The Wildcats outrebounded the Raiders 32-24.
